# Cargamos librerÃ­as
library(tidyverse)
library(tidytext)
library(wordcloud2)
library(igraph) 
library(ggraph) 

# Leemos archivo
trump <- read.csv("C:/Users/xviva/OneDrive/Desktop/trump.csv") 
trump <- trump[,-1] %>%
  mutate_at(vars(target), factor)
# Palabras mÃ¡s frecuentes en la columna 'insult'
trump %>%
  unnest_tokens(word, insult) %>%
  anti_join(stop_words) %>%
  count(word) %>%
  arrange(desc(n)) %>%
  head(n=10) %>%
  ggplot(aes(x=reorder(word, n), y=n)) +
  geom_col() +
  coord_flip() +
  labs(x="Most common words", y="n") +
  theme_bw()

# Wordcloud
freq <- trump %>%
  unnest_tokens(word, insult) %>%
  anti_join(stop_words) %>%
  count(word) %>%
  arrange(desc(n))

# Wordcloud de la columna 'insult'
# QuerÃ­a hacer un wordcloud con la forma de la silueta de Trump. En teorÃ­a se puede, en Kaggle 
# tengo algÃºn ejemplo, pero este paquete siempre da muchos problemas...
wordcloud2(freq, size=1)
# Bigrams mÃ¡s frecuentes en la columna 'insult'
bigrams <- trump %>%
  unnest_tokens(word, insult, token="ngrams", n=2) %>%
  filter(!is.na(word)) %>%
  separate(word, c("word1", "word2"), sep=" ") %>% 
  filter(!word1 %in% stop_words$word,
         !word2 %in% stop_words$word) %>% 
  unite(word,word1, word2, sep=" ") %>% 
  anti_join(stop_words) %>%
  count(word) 

bigrams %>%
  arrange(desc(n)) %>%
  head(n=10) %>%
  ggplot(aes(x=reorder(word, n), y=n)) +
  geom_col() +
  coord_flip() +
  labs(x="Most common bigrams", y="n") +
  theme_bw()

# Grafo con bigrams
bigrams_separated <- bigrams %>%
  separate(word, c("word1", "word2"), sep=" ")

bigrams_graph <- bigrams_separated %>%
  filter(n>15) %>%
  graph_from_data_frame() 
  
set.seed(2016)

# Create and draw arrows 
a <- grid::arrow(type="closed", length=unit(0.15, "inches"))

# ggraph visualization
ggraph(bigrams_graph, layout="fr") +
  geom_edge_link(aes(edge_alpha=n), show.legend = FALSE,
                 arrow=a, end_cap=circle(0.07, 'inches')) +
  geom_node_point(color="lightblue", size=5) +
  geom_node_text(aes(label=name), vjust=1, hjust=1) +
  theme_void()

# Trigrams mÃ¡s frecuentes en la columna 'insult'
trigrams <- trump %>%
  unnest_tokens(word, insult, token="ngrams", n=3) %>%
  filter(!is.na(word)) %>%
  separate(word, c("word1", "word2", "word3"), sep=" ") %>%
  filter(!word1 %in% stop_words$word,
         !word2 %in% stop_words$word,
         !word3 %in% stop_words$word) %>%
  unite(word,word1, word2, word3, sep=" ") %>% 
  anti_join(stop_words) %>%
  count(word) 

trigrams %>%
  arrange(desc(n)) %>%
  head(n=10) %>%
  ggplot(aes(x=reorder(word, n), y=n)) +
  geom_col() +
  coord_flip() +
  labs(x="Most common trigrams", y="n") +
  theme_bw()

# Palabras mÃ¡s frecuentes de la columna 'insult' a sus 10 primeros target
trump %>%
  filter(target %in% c("the-media", "democrats", "hillary-clinton", "trump-russia",
                       "joe-biden", "the-new-york-times", "cnn", "impeachment-inquiry",
                       "2020-election", "adam-schiff")) %>%
  unnest_tokens(word, insult) %>%
  anti_join(stop_words) %>%
  select(target, word) %>%
  count(target, word) %>%
  group_by(target) %>%
  top_n(10) %>%
  ggplot(aes(x=reorder(word, n), y=n)) +
  geom_col() +
  coord_flip() +
  theme_bw() +
  facet_wrap(~target, scales="free") +
  labs(x="Most common words")
